properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 12 at 2:01PM PST until February 14 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...South 15 to 15 knots Thursday. West winds Thursday night
20 to 30 kt.

* WHERE...Central U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca and East
Entrance U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca.

* WHEN...From 9 AM Thursday to 4 AM PST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 21 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or higher are expected to produce hazardous
wave conditions to small craft. Inexperienced mariners,
especially those operating smaller vessels should avoid
navigating in these conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM THURSDAY TO 4 AM PST FRIDAY
